# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1987-kentucky-derby
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] The **1875 Kentucky Derby** was the first running of the annually recurring race, taking place on May 17, 1875.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] It took place on the Louisville Jockey Club Grounds as a 1.5-mile run.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] The track was not called Churchill Downs until 1884 and the traditional distance of 1.25 miles was not established until 1896.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] That first Derby was a 1.5-mile race, and the traditional distance of 1.25 miles was not established until the 1896 Derby.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] For the first several years the betting format at this race was as auction pools in which people bid for the right to bet on the horse and the highest bidder then placed his bet.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] The bettor who picked the winning horse won the whole pot.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] Thirteen of the fifteen jockeys in the race, including winner Oliver Lewis, were African-American.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] The winner was Aristides, by two lengths.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] Aristides' half-brother and stablemate Chesapeake also ran in the race.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] Both Aristides' jockey and trainer were black.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] Aristides's time of 2 minutes and 37.75 seconds was at the time a world record for the distance.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1875-kentucky-derby] The second-place finisher received $200.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1876-kentucky-derby] The **1876 Kentucky Derby** was the 2nd running of that annually recurring race.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1876-kentucky-derby] It took place on May 15, 1876, on the Louisville Jockey Club grounds.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1876-kentucky-derby] Vagrant, the winning horse, won carrying only 97 pounds.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1877-kentucky-derby] The **1877 Kentucky Derby** was the 3rd running of the Kentucky Derby.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1877-kentucky-derby] The 1877 Derby was the first to attract a major celebrity spectator, Polish actress Helena Modjeska.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1877-kentucky-derby] Mint juleps, sometimes associated with the Derby, were first served at this race to Modjeska.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1877-kentucky-derby] Baden-Baden, the horse that won, went on to win the Travers Stakes, one of only ten horses to do this.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1877-kentucky-derby] William Walker, his jockey, was one of the Black jockeys who dominated the sport in the South after the Civil war.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1877-kentucky-derby] He went on to become a respected expert and advisor on Thoroughbred and attended every Derby for the rest of his life.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1878-kentucky-derby] The **1878 Kentucky Derby** was the 4th running of the Kentucky Derby.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1878-kentucky-derby] Winning horse Day Star set a new Kentucky Derby record with a winning time of 2:37.25.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1878-kentucky-derby] He also led the pack from start to finish, a first for the Derby.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1878-kentucky-derby] However, the most notable horse was the heavily favored Himyar.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1878-kentucky-derby] He had a bad start at the gate and the rest of the pack was ten lengths ahead before he got started.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1878-kentucky-derby] However, he passed all of them except Day Star, who he trailed by only two lengths at the finish line.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1878-kentucky-derby] This was the year that pari-mutuel betting was introduced to the Derby from France.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1879-kentucky-derby] The **1879 Kentucky Derby** was the 5th running of the Kentucky Derby.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1879-kentucky-derby] The winning horse Lord Murphy set a new Derby record with a winning time of 2:37.00.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1879-kentucky-derby] Lord Murphy was not the first horse out of the starting gate.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1879-kentucky-derby] He then dramatically collided with another horse and stumbled badly.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1879-kentucky-derby] However he recovered and achieved his note-worthy finish.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1879-kentucky-derby] He was the first horse foaled in Tennessee to win the Derby.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1879-kentucky-derby] Two more natives of that state would go on to win future Derbys.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] The **1880 Kentucky Derby** was the 6th running of the annually-recurring race.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] A dry spell stretching from late April to race day left the track with thick dust that obscured the horses from view for part of the race.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] That dust is credited with helping Fonso win the race.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] His early lead kept him in front of it as it partially obscured the vision of the horses behind him.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] Though he won, he was not really considered an exceptional horse.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] Remarkably, his owner sold him for about $2500 after the summer races in Lexington.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] This race was the first in which a jockey at the Derby officially registered a complaint with the stewards.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] Billy Lakeland claimed a foul against Fonso.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] However, his complaint was not supported.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1880-kentucky-derby] Fonso's jockey was Garret Lewis, a Black rider who was part of the group Blacks who dominated the sport in the South and border states after the Civil War.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1881-kentucky-derby] The **1881 Kentucky Derby** was the 7th running of the Kentucky Derby.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1987-kentucky-derby] The **1987 Kentucky Derby** was the 113th running of the Kentucky Derby.
[src:1987-kentucky-derby/1987-kentucky-derby] The race took place on May 2, 1987, with 130,532 people in attendance.
